text: Chrishall is a village and civil parish in Uttlesford, Essex, England. In 2001 there were 507 people living in Chrishall. It has a church called Holy Trinity. Other names for Chrishall include Chrisshall, Cresshall, and Cryotissale. == References == Category:Uttlesford Category:Villages in Essex Category:Civil parishes in Essex
